CYP450 3A4 inhibitor, a progressive dosage reduction may be required over a longer period if the corticosteroid is to be withdrawn from therapy, as there may be a significant risk of adrenal suppression.', 'Metabolism', 'The possibility of increased corticosteroid effects should be considered during coadministration with potent and moderate CYP450 3A4 inhibitors.', 'Moderate', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/120962/', '', 'Fluconazole, Caspofungin, Amphotericin B, Micafungin, Oteseconazole, Flucytosine, Anidulafungin', 'Mupirocin, Mometasone furoate, Epinephrine, Vitamin A, Ephedrine, Olopatadine, Ipratropium, Cromoglicic acid, Hyaluronic acid, Nedocromil, Phenylephrine, More', 1767369485);
